	<div id="content">
		<h2>About Me!
	</h2>
	I am a PhD student in the <a href = "www.cs.pitt.edu">CS department</a> of <a href = "www.pitt.edu">PITT</a>. I joined the department in 2011. My advisor is
	<a href="http://people.cs.pitt.edu/~litman/" rel="external" target="_blank">Prof. Litman</a>.
	
	<br>
	<br>My interest involves Natural Language Processing and Human Computer Interaction. My current research focuses on using NLP techniques for revision analysis.  
 
	<br>
	<br>
	<a name="“#education”"></a>
	<h2>Education</h2>
	Before I came to the United States, I stayed in Wuhan University for 6 years for my Bachelor and Master's degree. My undergraduate major is software engineering. My master study is done in State Key Lab of Software Engineering instructed by Prof. Shi Ying (应时).   

